🖼️ Part 2 — Create an AMI (Amazon Machine Image):
        💡 What is AMI? It is a snapshot/template of your entire EC2 instance — OS, 
          installed software, configurations — used to launch identical instances quickly.
        
        Step 1 — Create Image:
                Go to EC2 → Instances
                Right-click on second instance
                Click "Image and Templates" → "Create Image"
        Step 2 — Configure the Image:
        -------------------------------------------------------
        Setting	      Value
        Image Name	   DemoImageAMI
        Description	  AMI with httpd installed
        --------------------------------------------------------
        Click "Create Image" ✅
        💡 The AMI will now appear under AMIs in the left panel. It may take a few minutes to become Available

=====================================================================================================================
🚀 Part 3 — Launch a New Instance from AMI:
            Step 1 — Navigate to AMIs:
                    In the left panel → Click "AMIs"
                    Select DemoImageAMI
                    Click "Launch Instance from AMI"
            Step 2 — Configure the Instance:
            ---------------------------------------------------------
            Setting	            Value
            OS Images	          Go to "My AMIs" tab → "Owned by Me" → Select DemoImageAMI
            Instance Type	      t2.micro
            Key Pair	          EC2Tutorial1
            Security Group	    launch-wizard-1
            -----------------------------------------------------------
            Step 3 — Add User Data:
                    Expand "Advanced Details"
                    Scroll down to "User Data"
                    Paste the following script:
            
            Copy
            bash
            #!/bin/bash
            # Use this for your user data (script from top to bottom)
            # httpd is already installed via AMI
            # Just create the Hello World webpage
            echo "<h1>Hello World from $(hostname -f)</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
            Click "Launch Instance" ✅
            Step 4 — Result:
            
            Open browser → http://<EC2-Public-IP>
            You will see → "Hello World from <hostname>" ✅
